    },
    {
      "id": "f84000",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The two neighbors who had volunteered the most with me chose to move to different schools where their boys would not be outsiders. My public shaming after all the years of volunteer work convinced them that their young white boys were not welcome at the school. I understand and respect their choices. It still makes me sad. When I turned to local activism, I hoped to have a tangible influence. But this outcome is not what I had in mind."
